# Discussion {.center}

## Discussion

::: v-center-container
> Probability is just calculus for counting
:::

## Discussion

::: v-center-container
> The frequentist approach requires that all probabilities be defined by connection to the frequencies of events in very large samples
:::

## Discussion

::: v-center-container
> From the perspective of our \[statistical\] golem, the coin toss is 'random', but it's really the golem that is random, not the coin
:::

## Discussion

::: v-center-container
> Do animals/humans reason in a Bayesian way?
:::

